definition: to withdraw from a political party
to retreat/to decline/to move back/to withdraw

sentences.english: And Yasuhisa Shiozaki, a former chief cabinet secretary, has not accepted Mr Watanabe's entreaties to join him.
sentences.chinese: 前官房長官鹽崎恭久也拒絕了渡邊一同退黨的要求。

sentences.english: Feinstein refused to get in line, was sacked and eventually left the party.
sentences.chinese: 費恩斯坦拒絕妥協，因此被炒了魷魚，並最終退黨。

sentences.english: One Democratic Party legislator quit the party in protest.
sentences.chinese: 而一位民主黨立法者因反對這一方案而退黨。
